                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.002 Hitler, Adolf/21: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-08T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 8, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. Department’s 29, March 6, 1 p.m. At the press conference today a
                    correspondent inquired whether the Under Secretary had any comments to make on
                    the mock trial entitled “Hitler versus Civilization” held at the Madison Square
                    Garden last night.</p>
                <p>Mr. Phillips replied that he had no comment other than to re-emphasize the
                    private nature of the gathering and that no member of the Administration was
                    present. Anything that was said therefore represented the personal views of the
                    individual speakers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
